body: Second page of the Android Studio 4.2 wizard looks like this. @devoncarew @pq may have ideas for improvement. The IntelliJ view is similar but includes a Project Type selector. Instead of running `flutter config` this reads the settings file directly. It is much faster. Also, instead of running `flutter channel` this runs the git command directly. We need to add unit tests to `flutter_tools` that document which fields we depend on from the settings file. We should also have a test that warns `flutter_tools` authors that if the locations of the settings file changes that IDE authors need to be notified. The check boxes still need to be added to the wizard used by AS 4.1. That is a separate project, which may resolve itself when 4.2 becomes stable. Line 26 of CONTRIBUTING.md documents the additional dependency on git4idea.

comment_data.body: I don't know if that's actually intended or if the flutter tool would pay attention to that.
It doesn't. But if someone went to that much trouble we should initialize the checkboxes to respect the setting, I think.

I wasn't sure how verbose we should be. I considered adding another line with some explanation, and think I'll do that now. However, I misunderstood the purpose of the config file. I'm going to have to rewrite some of this. Instead of enabling check boxes based on platforms enabled in the config file it seems those should be the ones checked by default. All should be enabled.
